public class PowerOfThree {
    public static boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n > 1) {
            if (n % 3 == 0) {
                count++;
                n /= 3;
            } else {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return count == 1;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(27)); // Output: true
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(0)); // Output: false
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(-1)); // Output: false
    }
}
```

This solution uses an iterative approach to check if n is a power of three. It repeatedly divides n by 3 until it reaches 1 and counts the number of times the division was successful (i.e., n % 3 == 0). If the count is equal to 1, then n is a power of three. Otherwise, it returns false.

